Twenty-five political parties have declared that they will support the candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in the Bauchi South Senatorial District bye-election slated for August 11. Addressing a press conference in Bauchi on Saturday, the state chairman of African Peoples Alliance (APA), Comrade Abdullahi B. Muhammad said that the decision to support the APC candidate was because they were satisfied with his performance as a serving federal lawmaker. He added that their action was also based on their support for the APC-led administration in Bauchi State to continue with its vision of bringing meaningful development in all parts of the state. Alhaji Lawal Yahaya Gumau, Member representing Toro Federal Constituency in the House of Representatives emerged APC candidate for Bauchi South Senatorial District bye-election.